<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7459] CqlRecordWriter doesn&apos;t close socket connections</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7459</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using spark with `CqlOutputFormat` results in thousands of open connections to cassandra (and then crashes unless they get garbage collected fast enough). This is because  each save to cassandra task creates a `CqlRecordWriter` which opens a bunch of connections but calling close on those writers does not actually close their socket connections to cassandra.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
